Ad Text:
About Us

At Agile Insights, we are passionate about empowering organisations to transform through the power of Data & AI. We work with global brands and leading organisations to deliver innovative solutions that solve real business challenges. We have a fantastic, long-standing relationship with Microsoft. We are extremely proud to be a Microsoft Solutions Specialist for four competencies including: Data Analytics and AI, Azure and Digital & App Innovation.

Your Role

Organisations in every industry are looking to AI technologies to solve a range of business problems and improve efficiency and quality across the board. As a Senior Azure AI Consultant, your primary focus will be designing, coding, and deploying AI-infused applications on Azure using cutting-edge services like Azure OpenAI, Azure AI Search, and Azure Cognitive Services (vision, speech, language).

You will work with business stakeholders and executives to paint the art of the possible, help them understand where AI can help their organisations innovate, prioritize AI use cases based on business impact and feasibility, and built roadmaps to successful project delivery. You will work closely with customer business and technical teams to architect and deliver the solution, being the primary hands-on-keyboard developer for the solution.

You will dive deep into development, transforming complex requirements into robust, scalable code while integrating Azure AI services to build intelligent, data-driven solutions. From writing and testing code to optimizing performance and ensuring security compliance, you will be at the forefront of crafting innovative AI applications. You’ll lead the technical aspects of projects, taking them through architecture and security reviews, thoroughly documenting solutions, and ensuring smooth technical handovers. This role emphasizes deep technical work, creative problem solving, and collaboration with technical teams to bring AI projects to life from concept to deployment.

You will Bring

Consulting skills - requirements gathering, documentation, stakeholder management
Hands-on-keyboard software development experience
Real-world on-the tools all day-every day Azure apps skills
Passion for moving into AI development

What We’re Looking For

Experience building web applications on Azure in .NET (or Python) and JavaScript frameworks (React Preferred).
Background in technical consulting & delivery roles.
Experience with LLM development (OpenAI, Semantic Kernel, Langchain, etc)
Knowledge of the wider Azure AI landscape and tools (e.g. Azure AI Search, Cognitive Services)
Experience designing and architecting applications using Azure cloud-native components including AppService, Functions, LogicApps, etc.
Azure Integration Services experience will be highly valued.
Strong knowledge of data technologies including SQL, Cosmos and Fabric
Broad knowledge of cloud-based architectures and principles (security, networking)
Keen for a fast-paced environment with the opportunities to learn, grow and be exposed to a variety of problems, clients and technologies.
Ability to understand client requirements and transform into working solutions.
Ability to work remotely via Microsoft Teams
Aptitude for critical and analytical thinking, as well as the capacity to leverage out-of-the box solutions
Employment basis: Permanent, full time, Hybrid, ideally located in Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide or Melbourne.

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.
Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.
Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications.
Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event.
Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive.
Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases.
Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms.
Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries.
Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI.
Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

No Agencies - No overseas applications - Must be in Australia and have full work rights

Through the merger of Bank Australia and Qudos Bank we’re creating a better, stronger and more resilient bank for our customers and employees. As one company with two trusted brands, we’re building on the strong foundations of our history and shared values as we bring together the best of both banks.

As a Senior Analyst – Fraud Detection & Prevention, you’ll play a key role in protecting Bank Australia and its customers from financial crime. Using data analytics, modelling and reporting, you’ll identify fraud trends, support regulatory initiatives, and help shape effective threat response strategies. Working closely with internal and external stakeholders, you’ll ensure the bank remains proactive and compliant in an evolving financial crime landscape.

Why join us

We have big plans to become Australia’s leading purpose-driven bank.
As a certified B Corp, we’re part of a global business community who meet the highest social and environmental standards, balancing profit and purpose.
Every role and person in our bank is essential to bringing our values, purpose and aspiration to life.
We offer flexible working options, competitive salary and 13% super.
Our staff have access to a range of meaningful benefits to support their physical and mental wellbeing including 24/7 free counselling, free flu vaccinations and discounted gym memberships.
We also support staff with study assistance, paid parental leave (regardless of gender), volunteer, bereavement, gender affirmation and family violence leave; and the opportunity for bonus annual leave.
We support our staff to grow their careers through learning and development and an organisational culture where we reward and recognise innovation and values, not long hours.
We are committed to building an inclusive culture and a diverse workforce that reflects the Australian community.
We care for a conservation reserve – where we work with key partner organisations to protect threatened species and involve staff in conservation.

What you will be doing

Analyse fraud trends and implement detection strategies using data mining and modelling
Optimise existing controls to balance fraud risk and customer experience
Assess financial crime cases to inform control design and prevention strategies
Contribute to fraud prevention initiatives using insights from analytics
Support projects with requirements, testing and change management input
Conduct data analysis to support business decisions
Develop clear and accurate reporting to support fraud oversight

What you will bring

Relevant tertiary qualification in statistics, business, financial crime or similar
Extensive experience in banking, with a focus on fraud analytics and prevention
Strong data analysis skills, including experience with data mining and modelling
Experience developing fraud detection rules and mentoring analysts
Advanced communication, numeracy and data visualisation skills (Power BI preferred)
Ability to interpret technical concepts and generate actionable insights
Strong stakeholder engagement and ability to influence without authority
Knowledge of financial crime legislation and regulatory obligations
Results-driven, organised and able to work independently under pressure
Commitment to Bank Australia’s values and customer wellbeing
Commitment to Bank Australia’s purpose, aspiration, values and brand as well as the B Corp ethos.

By submitting an application you agree to Bank Australia’s Privacy Policy for applicants and confirm that you are legally able to work in Australia. Bank Australia is an equal opportunity employer committed to sustainable development. We encourage people from different backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from different cultural backgrounds and people with disabilities because we want to reflect the diversity of our communities. We are committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process and supportive workplace.

Bank Australia reserves the right to withdraw this advertisement at any time. Candidates will be progressed as applications are received, rather than after the advertisement closure date. If you wish to be considered, please submit your application as soon as possible. Please note, the successful candidate will be subject to satisfactory background checks including but not limited to police and previous employment.

Collaborate with stakeholders to shape future-state HR solutions
Influence HCM platform selection and drive best practice adoption
Attractive hybrid work model | Energy Discounts |9-month contract 

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

About the role

Join our Corporate Technology Project team as a strategic SME in Human Capital Management on a 9-month fixed term contract. You’ll play a critical part in our HCM transformation initiative, providing expert analysis and insights to assess current HR capabilities, identify gaps, and support the selection of a new HCM technical platform aligned to our future-state HR operating model.

Why you’ll love working here

We’re a welcoming bunch who put our energy into being the best company we can be. For us, this means shared respect, great communication between teams, acting on our ideas, and looking out for each other’s wellbeing. There are plenty of great perks, from flexible working to a long list of exclusive Alinta benefits.

What you’ll do

Reviewing the comprehensive gap analysis and process mapping conducted across HR functions
Collaborating with HR, IT, and business stakeholders to validate the requirements and identify new requirement based on past knowledge and experience 
Translating business needs into functional specifications for HCM platform selection
Supporting vendor evaluation, RFPs, demos, and scoring frameworks
Developing clear documentation and presenting recommendations to executives

Your experience

Proven experience as a Subject Matter Expert in HCM platforms (e.g., Workday, SAP SuccessFactors, Oracle HCM)
Strong understanding of end-to-end HR business processes and service delivery models
Demonstrated experience in gap analysis and enterprise system selection
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills
Experience in large-scale HR transformation or system implementation projects

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

This is your chance to make a real impact in a fast-paced, collaborative environment. If you thrive on challenge and want to play a role in shaping the future of HR, we want to hear from you!

Like what you’re seeing?

If you like the sound of this, and you’ve got experience in a similar role, we’d love to talk to you. Come and discover better together with Alinta Energy.

We are a 2025 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.

If your application progresses, we will need to complete background and pre-employment checks, such as immigration checks, reference checks, criminal background checks, qualification checks, and additional checks for roles related to finance.

Our Diversity Commitment

Alinta Energy offers a truly diverse, safe and supportive work environment. As an equal opportunity employer, Alinta Energy encourages applications from any qualified person, including First Nations Australians, members of the LGBTQIA+ community, people of all ages and people living with a disability. We are also proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer and we are committed to advancing women’s careers.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Click ‘Apply’ to submit your application.

Job Title: Senior Analyst or Manager - JSOX Implementation
Ad Text:
Senior Analyst/Manager – JSOX Compliance Project 9-Month Contract | Immediate Start
Are you an experienced compliance or risk professional ready to take on a high-impact project? Our client is seeking a skilled Senior Analyst or Manager to lead the implementation of a JSOX compliance framework over a 9-month contract. This is a unique opportunity to play a critical role in driving governance and compliance outcomes within a dynamic environment.

About the Opportunity
In this contract role, you’ll be responsible for managing the end-to-end delivery of a JSOX compliance implementation project. Working closely with senior stakeholders, you’ll provide expertise in internal controls, risk management, and regulatory compliance while ensuring the project meets quality, timeliness, and reporting requirements.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives in project-based work, enjoys engaging with multiple stakeholders, and has a strong understanding of compliance frameworks within complex organisations.

Key Responsibilities
Lead the design, development, and implementation of JSOX compliance processes and controls
Engage and collaborate with internal teams and external advisors to ensure best practice delivery
Monitor project timelines, budgets, and reporting milestones to achieve successful outcomes
Provide guidance, training, and support to business units on JSOX requirements
Conduct testing, documentation, and assurance activities to validate compliance effectiveness
Present findings, updates, and recommendations to senior leadership
About You We are looking for someone with:

Proven experience in compliance, risk management, or internal audit, ideally with JSOX or SOX exposure
Strong project management skills with the ability to manage competing priorities
Excellent communication skills to influence and engage stakeholders at all levels
Analytical mindset with a detail-oriented approach
A collaborative and proactive working style
How to Apply If you’re ready to bring your expertise to a pivotal compliance project, we’d love to hear from you. Please click Apply Now and submit your CV outlining your relevant experience. Alternatively you can contact Fraser Chapman on fraser.chapman@talentweb.com.au or 0424 155 675

Corporate Strategy Manager, you will be responsible for shaping the strategic direction of a leading financial services organisation. You'll work closely with executives and senior leaders to identify strategic opportunities, mitigate risks, and drive key initiatives. This role is vital in helping the company fulfill its purpose of supporting Australians in their time of need.
Your key responsibilities will include:

Corporate Strategy: Co-develop and refine the corporate strategy, ensuring it aligns with the company's long-term goals and market dynamics.
 
Strategic Planning: Play a key role in the annual strategic planning process, including organizing and driving strategy off-sites for the executive team and the board.
 
Market Analysis: Conduct in-depth market analysis, competitor benchmarking, and industry trend assessments to identify emerging trends and opportunities.
 
Strategic Analysis and Insights: Build and manage complex models to support strategic projects and extract insights from large data sets.
 
Stakeholder Management: Develop and maintain relationships with key stakeholders, including executives, senior leaders, business managers, and external partners.
 
Key Requirements   
This role is well-suited for candidates with a strong background in strategy consulting or corporate strategy within the financial services sector.

Required Skills and Qualifications:

A bachelor's degree or higher in business, commerce, engineering, or a related field, with an MBA being highly regarded.
 
At least three years of experience in strategy consulting or corporate strategy roles within the financial services industry.
 
Exceptional written communication and presentation skills, with the ability to simplify complex data for senior audiences, including boards.
 
Strong analytical and Excel skills to translate complex data into actionable insights.
 
A passion for problem-solving and a drive to achieve results.

Salary: Competitive salary package, with range of benefits
Ad Text:
Why Edge Impact?

At Edge Impact, our mission is simple and ambitious: to create a world where unsustainable is unthinkable.

We’re a team of passionate, collaborative, and courageous people who partner with leading businesses across industries to deliver positive global impact. We do this through the power of science, strategy, and storytelling, combining evidence, actionable plans, and inspiration to drive real change.

When you join Edge, you’ll work alongside smart, kind humans who care deeply about creating a better future for our clients, communities, and the world.

The Role and Why You’ll Love Working With Us

Climate and decarbonisation reporting is reshaping how organisations understand their risks and opportunities — and how they prepare for the future. Businesses are looking for advisors who bring rigour, clarity and practical direction to these challenges.

As a Managing Consultant, Decarbonisation, you’ll play a pivotal role in helping clients design and deliver credible pathways to net zero. You’ll lead the development of decarbonisation strategies, apply robust mitigation modelling, and support organisations to meet emerging disclosure requirements (ASRS, ISSB, SBTs).

This role is ideal for someone who’s ready to step into a broader leadership remit — leading project delivery, supporting business growth, mentoring junior team members and shaping the future of decarbonisation advisory at Edge.

You’ll report to the Head of Decarbonisation and work closely with colleagues across Climate & Nature, ESG and Circular Economy. Every project you lead will contribute to a bigger purpose: enabling clients to accelerate their transition to a sustainable, low-carbon future.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the design and execution of decarbonisation strategies and transition plans.
Apply mitigation modelling and analysis, ensuring rigour and quality.
Manage large client accounts spanning multiple Edge service lines.
Build client capacity in climate disclosure, reporting and strategy.
Stay ahead of industry and regulatory trends, translating them into practical outcomes.
Contribute to thought leadership, proposals and partnerships that extend our impact.
Mentor and support consultants and analysts within the team.

What we’re looking for
A degree in Environmental Science, Engineering, Economics, Sustainability, Sustainable Finance or a related field.
Strong data analysis and modelling skills (advanced Excel; PowerBI, R, or similar an advantage).
Experience in emissions reduction strategies, climate transition planning, and/or disclosure frameworks.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to engage senior stakeholders.
A collaborative, adaptable leader who thrives in a multidisciplinary environment.
Genuine passion for creating meaningful change for people, nature, and climate.
Commercial acumen and client advisory experience, including direct engagement with senior stakeholders
Proven ability to guide and mentor junior team members
Strong written and verbal communication skills, clear, concise, and impactful



At Edge Impact, diversity is our strength. We encourage applicants from all backgrounds and walks of life to bring their whole selves to work.

Ready to accelerate the transition to net zero?

Apply now and help shape the future of decarbonisation with Edge Impact.

Applications close Friday, 20 October 2025

Primary purpose of the role
Lead and manage the delivery of strategic programs and initiatives to ensure alignment with priorities and objectives, maximise stakeholder and customer value and support the achievement of customer-centric outcomes.

Key accountabilities
Provide expert, strategic advice to senior leaders and other key customers and stakeholders on service improvements, strategic programs, and emerging program issues and risks, to inform evidence-based decision making and drive improved customer outcomes.

Lead the development, implementation, and evaluation of organisational strategic programs and initiatives, identifying interdependencies and leveraging resources to maximise efficiencies and achieve desired outcomes.

Provide direction and expert advice to customers and stakeholder on strategic initiatives and programs to ensure compliance with all statutory and legal requirements and delivery of required outcomes.

Collaborate and engage with specialist teams to ensure the application of best practice methodologies to achieve improved efficiencies.

Manage customer and stakeholder relationships through effective communication, collaboration, negotiation, and issues management to ensure effective engagement throughout strategy development and implementation.

Facilitate workshops and deliver presentations, to influence, educate and inform senior leaders and influential stakeholders throughout all stages of strategy development and implementation.

Key knowledge and experience
Substantial experience in leading the development and implementation of strategic programs.

Project Management
Structure, drafting, gathering requirements and formatting strategies
Writing Business Cases
$1,250 per day
Start date asap and finishing date being scheduled for 6 months

At Escient, we believe the most meaningful success is the kind that’s shared. We’re a purpose-led consultancy, helping organisations navigate complexity, embrace change, and deliver positive impact for people, society, and the planet.

We’re looking for Senior Consultants with a background in Business Analysis or Project Management and who have experience working in banking and finance, to bring their expertise, empathy, and collaborative spirit to our team.

We’re proud to be a Certified B Corporation and a multi-year Employer of Choice. Our culture is built on:

Selflessness – we put people first, always.

Courage – we act with integrity, even when it’s hard.

Creativity – we look at challenges differently, finding better ways forward.

Empathy – we listen deeply, understand perspectives, and turn insight into action.

At Escient, you’ll be part of a diverse, inclusive team where your voice is valued, your growth is supported, and your work creates real impact.




Responsibilities

What you’ll do

· Partner with clients in the banking and finance sector, shaping solutions that create lasting value.

· Build trusted relationships with senior stakeholders through clarity, empathy, and collaboration.

· Apply your skills as a Business Analyst (requirements, process design, customer journeys) or Project Manager (planning, governance, delivery leadership).

· Bring structure and calm to complexity, helping clients move forward with confidence.

· Contribute to Escient’s culture of connection, curiosity, and courageous thinking.




Requirements

What you bring

· Experience as a BA or PM in banking and finance (consulting experience highly regarded).

· Strong relationship building and communication skills; you know how to listen, include, and inspire.

· A track record of guiding teams and stakeholders to shared outcomes.

· A growth mindset, with the humility to learn and the confidence to share your perspective.

· Alignment with our values and a passion for making work more human and purposeful.




Benefits

What we offer

· A people-first culture where better experiences drive better results.

· Opportunities to shape your career across industries, clients, and disciplines.

· A supportive, inclusive environment that celebrates diversity of thought and background.

· The chance to do meaningful work that leaves a positive mark on organisations and communities.

· Our commitment to our people is reflected in the comprehensive range of professional development and financial benefits we provide. These include flexible working arrangements, an annual BYOD technology and professional membership allowance, the option to purchase additional annual leave, paid parental leave, and the unique opportunity to become an Escient shareholder through our employee scheme.




How to apply

If this sounds like the right next step for you, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply at www.escientjobs.careers.flair.hr to join a team where courage, creativity, and empathy drive real change. Make sure to include your CV and a cover letter telling us why you want to work for Escient and how you connect to our values.

This role is not about maintaining the status quo — it’s about shaping the future. With executive-level visibility, you’ll be tasked with designing and embedding a strategy that elevates data into a true competitive advantage.

Ad Text:
Are you passionate about shaping the future of work through data, technology, and people-centred design? This leadership role offers the opportunity to redefine how people systems and insights enable a thriving workforce and drive organisational performance.

In this role, you lead the strategy, integration and optimisation of people systems, insights and analytics to create seamless digital employee experiences, enable data-informed decision-making, and strengthen strategic workforce planning. Your work will directly influence the organisation's ability to deliver on its purpose and values while building a sustainable, future-ready workforce.

Key activities

Guide and empower a high-performing team specialising in people systems (HRIS), workforce intelligence, and data enabled insights.
Foster innovation, human-centred design, continuous improvement, and a mindset of curiosity across the People & Culture function.
Oversee the lifecycle of HR systems, ensuring they are intuitive, integrated, and optimised for an exceptional employee experience.
Assist in teh design and delivery a people analytics program that provides proactive, predictive, and actionable insights for leaders.
Identify future workforce needs and risks, ensuring data-driven strategies are embedded into organisational planning.

Previous experience working in a HR/People & Culture function focusing on people systems, insights, and workforce planning.

A new opportunity is open for a Senior Algorithm Engineer to join a high-performance development team working on real-time RF and AI-based sensing systems. This role is ideal for an experienced engineer who enjoys turning advanced theory into practical solutions that operate at the edge.
  
The role involves designing, integrating, and optimising complex algorithms to power intelligent sensor platforms deployed in operational environments. It requires deep collaboration with software engineers, systems designers, and UI developers to ensure algorithmic outputs are both efficient and actionable.

Key Responsibilities

Research and implement mathematical models and algorithms for deployment on edge computing platforms
Collaborate with software teams to optimise model integration within production architectures
Contribute to GUI discussions to ensure algorithmic outputs are user-friendly and visually intuitive
Manage data pipelines including multi-domain datasets, preparation, labelling, and validation
Maintain clean, well-documented codebases for sensor fusion and ML-driven software modules
Support decision-making across software and hardware teams for complex system evolution
Guide the integration of models into scalable, high-performance production environments
Skills and Experience Required

Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related technical field
Proven experience designing and integrating complex algorithms for sensor data or real-time systems
Familiarity with signal processing, time-series analysis, and sensor fusion techniques
Experience working with RF data or analysis tools is highly desirable
Strong grasp of probability, statistics, and their application in modelling
Competency with version control and Git workflows
Comfortable operating in Linux environments with modern toolchains
Desirable Attributes

Exposure to ML/AI workflows or model deployment practices
Familiarity with heterogeneous computing or GPU programming (CUDA)
Ability to turn business requirements into robust, interpretable algorithmic solutions
Strong communicator capable of bridging technical conversations across multidisciplinary teams
Passion for staying up to date with algorithmic advances and deploying real-world solutions
A hands-on mindset and motivation to contribute in a fast-paced, mission-driven environment
This is a unique opportunity to work at the intersection of advanced analytics, signal intelligence, and real-time systems, with tangible impact across defence, surveillance, and security domains.

For more info, feel free to contact me at farid@thedrivegroup.com.au or click Apply to send through your details and I'll be in touch.

Opportunity to lead and shape BA capability in a high-profile transformation program.

Join a values-driven organisation with a focus on innovation and improvement.

Ready to lead business analysis across impactful change programs?
Apply now to take the next step in your career.

Company description:



The Department of Education is the largest provider of public education in Australia with responsibility for delivering high-quality public education to two-thirds of the NSW student population. For more information about the Department of Education, please visit http://www.dec.nsw.gov.au/



Job description:


Two, Ongoing Full-Time roles
Location: Eveleigh with access to flexible working arrangements available
Salary: Clerk Grade 11/12 with base salary ranging from $149,739 to $173,174 per annum, plus employer's contribution to superannuation and annual leave loading

Ad Text:
The role:  

Queensland Health recognises that progressing our digital health strategy is an essential part of our ongoing commitment to delivering safe, effective, and accessible healthcare to all Queenslanders.

Queensland Health is currently undertaking several of the largest health ICT programs and projects ever seen in Australia. The largest of these, the Digital Hospital Program (DHP) is a visionary program that continues to enable clinical services and enhance our technological capability by extending the availability of the ieMR into more hospitals and community care venues. The Digital Hospital Program will deliver advanced ieMR to 5 Metro North hospitals over the first 5 years. In parallel Queensland Health will be adding over 2,811 additional hospital beds across the state, with four entirely new hospitals and expansions to 11 already world-class facilities.

Implementing an integrated electronic Medical Record (ieMR) across all public hospitals in Queensland is at the heart of our digital transformation and is essential to delivering care, closer to home.  Already used in numerous facilities today, the ieMR is improving care and patient outcomes by offering Queensland Health clinicians access to real-time clinical information for their patients, at point of care.

A Solution Delivery Analyst (Clinical) plays a critical role in bridging clinical and business needs and IT solutions across eHealth Queensland, providing strategic advice on project direction, facilitate business requirements, use case development, and detailed engagement with clinical and business stakeholders. The role includes mentoring business analysts whilst ensuring effective communication and stakeholder engagement.

Is this opportunity for you?


To perform successfully in this role, you must demonstrate:

Proven experience working in a clinical digital transformation designing or redesigning workflows, processes in a healthcare system.
Ability to lead and manage multiple large stakeholder and clinical groups to achieve positive outcomes.
Proven experience in setting the direction for and leading business analysis activities, and in clinical digital transformation process redesign and business case development activities in the health care industry, and intimate knowledge of healthcare processes specifically those used for clinical digital transformation.
Experience overseeing, managing and defining business analysis and process modelling activities for large scale complex organisations.
Proven excellent negotiation, consultation, facilitation and effective written and oral communication skills for use in complex program/ project environment.
Highly developed ability to manage staff and build client focused and effective teams providing high-quality services to clients

The following experience will be highly regarded:

Strong knowledge and prior experience working across ieMR in a clinical healthcare environment.

While experience in health care is not a mandatory requirement, we highly value candidates who have demonstrated relevant experience in clinical systems, health IT, or digital health. If your experience is in other sectors, please make sure to outline how your knowledge can transfer to the healthcare context.

To be considered for this exciting opportunity submit your CV or resume and a short statement (maximum 2 pages) addressing your experience in each of the key areas outlined above.

About eHealth Queensland:

eHealth Queensland is one of the largest Information Communication Technology operations in the state. It is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of information systems and technologies so that Queensland Health employees and health providers have access to information that supports the delivery of health care.

Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:

By joining eHealth Queensland you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success. 

You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:

Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading
Flexible working arrangements
Diverse work culture
Career training and development

To apply for this exciting opportunity, submit your resume and a short statement (maximum 2 pages) on how your experience, abilities, knowledge and personal qualities are relevant for the role, taking into account the key responsibilities and attributes noted in the ‘How you will be assessed' section of the role description.

About Us

At Agile Insights, we are passionate about empowering organisations to transform through the power of Data & AI. We work with global brands and leading organisations to deliver innovative solutions that solve real business challenges. We have a fantastic, long-standing relationship with Microsoft. We are extremely proud to be a Microsoft Solutions Specialist for four competencies including: Data Analytics and AI, Azure and Digital & App Innovation.

Your Role

Organisations in every industry are looking to AI technologies to solve a range of business problems and improve efficiency and quality across the board. As a Principal AI Consultant, you will play a pivotal role in designing, building, and deploying AI infused applications on Azure using services like Azure OpenAI, Azure AI Search and Azure Cognitive Services (vision, speech, language). You will work with business stakeholders and executives to paint the art of the possible, help them understand where AI can help their organisations innovate, prioritize AI use cases based on business impact and feasibility, and build roadmaps to successful project delivery. You will work closely with customer business and technical teams to architect and deliver the solution, being the primary hands-on-keyboard developer for the solution. You’ll take the project through architecture and security reviews, document the solution and ensure successful hand-over to customer technical teams.

You will Bring

Consulting skills – presales, requirements gathering, documentation, stakeholder management
Hands-on-keyboard software development experience
Real-world on-the tools all day-every day Azure apps skills
Passion for moving into AI development

Key responsibilities:

Solution Delivery

Paint the ‘art of the possible’ with the client, understand their business and requirements and translate that vision into an AI solution. Own the end-to-end delivery of Enterprise AI solutions from POC to production including managing internal and external stakeholders, project budget, timeline and a quality enterprise AI solution Responsible for the code-quality, infrastructure, security, scalability and maintainability of the solution and shepherding the solution through enterprise CAB and ARB processes.

Workshops and Enablement

Facilitate envisioning sessions and hands-on workshops to explore AI opportunities for clients, showcasing the potential of Microsoft AI technologies.

Technical Leadership

Provide expert guidance on Microsoft OpenAI and related technologies, serving as a trusted advisor to clients and internal teams.  Mentor and inspire technical teams, fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation.  Stay ahead of emerging trends and advancements in AI and Microsoft technologies, incorporating them into Agile Insights’ offerings.

Consulting & Client Engagement

Collaborate with clients to understand their unique challenges, translating business requirements into technical solutions.  Build strong relationships with stakeholders, ensuring alignment and satisfaction throughout the engagement lifecycle.  Provide thought leadership through whitepapers, blogs, and presentations, positioning Agile Insights as a leading Microsoft Data & AI partner. 

IP Creation and Innovation

Drive the development of proprietary accelerators, frameworks, and reusable assets to enhance delivery efficiency and solution impact.  Work with Agile Insights' teams to design and launch AI-powered products aligned with market needs and Microsoft’s ecosystem.  Collaborate with Microsoft and other partners to secure funding and co-develop innovative solutions. 

Practice Growth

Support pre-sales efforts by crafting proposals, developing demos, and estimating project delivery costs.  Contribute to Agile Insights' thought leadership by participating in industry events, panels, and conferences.  Build and nurture a network of client relationships, identifying opportunities to expand Agile Insights’ presence in the market. 

What We’re Looking For:

Experience building web applications on Azure in .NET (or Python) and JavaScript frameworks (React Preferred).
Background in technical consulting & delivery roles.
Experience with LLM development (OpenAI, Semantic Kernel, Langchain, etc) Knowledge of the wider Azure AI landscape and tools (e.g. Azure AI Search, Cognitive Services)
Experience designing and architecting applications using Azure cloud-native components including AppService, Functions, LogicApps, etc.
Azure Integration Services experience will be highly valued.
Strong knowledge of data technologies including SQL, Cosmos and Fabric
Broad knowledge of cloud-based architectures and principles (security, networking)
Keen for a fast-paced environment with the opportunities to learn, grow and be exposed to a variety of problems, clients and technologies.
Ability to understand client requirements and transform into working solutions.
Ability to work remotely via Microsoft Teams Aptitude for critical and analytical thinking, as well as the capacity to leverage out-of-the box solutions
Employment basis: Permanent, full time, Hybrid, ideally located in Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide or Melbourne.

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.
Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.
Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications.
Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event.
Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive.
Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases.
Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms. Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries. Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI. Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

No Agencies - No overseas applications - Must be in Australia and have full work rights
